BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 720.00 Td (While this guide cannot cover every historical development relevant to Building Community) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 705.50 Td (Resilience to Natural Hazards through Early-Warning Systems and Local Preparedness,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 691.00 Td (delegates should keep in mind that this issue did not emerge overnight. It is the product) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 676.50 Td (of decades of political, economic, and social developments whose consequences continue to) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 662.00 Td (shape the positions that Member States and delegations hold today.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 642.42 Td (Your research should trace how the issue has evolved over time: which events first) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 627.92 Td (brought it to international attention, which agreements or frameworks have already) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 613.42 Td (attempted to address it, and why — despite those efforts — it remains unresolved.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 598.92 Td (Understanding this history matters, because many of the proposals you will hear in) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 584.42 Td (committee are simply updated versions of ideas that have been tried before, with varying) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 569.92 Td (degrees of success.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 72 542.37 Td (IV. Current Situation and Key Issues) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 517.72 Td (Although every delegation will bring its own perspective to the table, most discussions) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 503.22 Td (on Building Community Resilience to Natural Hazards through Early-Warning Systems and) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 488.72 Td (Local Preparedness tend to revolve around a shared set of underlying tensions. As you) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 474.22 Td (prepare, consider how your delegation would respond to each of the following:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 454.65 Td (- Expanding access to early-warning systems in remote and under-resourced communities) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 435.07 Td (- Strengthening schools and hospitals so that they can withstand natural hazards) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 415.50 Td (- Encouraging youth participation in local disaster-preparedness planning) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 395.92 Td (- Sharing lessons learned between regions that face very different hazard profiles) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 376.35 Td (These issues are not exhaustive. You are encouraged to identify additional angles that) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 361.85 Td (are particularly relevant to the country, organisation, or actor your delegation) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 347.35 Td (represents.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 72 319.80 Td (V. Past International Action) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 295.15 Td (The international community has not been silent on Building Community Resilience to) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 280.65 Td (Natural Hazards through Early-Warning Systems and Local Preparedness. Earlier) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 266.15 Td (resolutions, conferences, and frameworks have laid important groundwork, even if) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 251.65 Td (implementation has often fallen short of what was promised. Research which instruments) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 237.15 Td (are most relevant to UNDRR — including any prior actions taken by this committee or the) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 222.65 Td (bodies it answers to — and consider honestly why those efforts succeeded, stalled, or) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 208.15 Td (failed outright. A strong proposal builds on this record rather than ignoring it.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 72 180.60 Td (VI. Bloc Positions) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 155.95 Td (Delegations facing this topic generally fall into broader groupings shaped by geography,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 141.45 Td (level of development, historical experience, and strategic interest. Rather than) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 126.95 Td (memorising a fixed list of blocs, ask yourself: what does my country gain or risk under) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 112.45 Td (each possible outcome? Who are my natural allies, and where might I find unexpected) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 72 97.95 Td (common ground with delegations I would not normally agree with? The strongest speeches) Tj ET
